description.value: Will determine if `value` is classified as a `Function` object. *
description.raw: @description Will determine if `value` is classified as a `Function` object. *

example.value:
console.log ( isFunction(/asdf/) ) // false

console.log( isFunction(class MyClass{}) ) // true

console.log ( isFunction(function * MyFunc() {}) ) // true

console.log ( isFunction(() => {}) ) // true

console.log ( isFunction(async () => {}) ) // true

console.log ( isFunction(Math.random) ) // true
example.raw:
@example

console.log ( isFunction(/asdf/) ) // false

console.log( isFunction(class MyClass{}) ) // true

console.log ( isFunction(function * MyFunc() {}) ) // true

console.log ( isFunction(() => {}) ) // true

console.log ( isFunction(async () => {}) ) // true

console.log ( isFunction(Math.random) ) // true

returns.description: Returns `true` if `value` is a function, else `false`.
returns.raw: @returns {boolean} Returns `true` if `value` is a function, else `false`.
